154,0.01185224,-0.03258696,0.04880483,0.00967259,0.02953745,-0.03953144,0.03805650,0.02251805,-0.01035999,-0.01271437,-0.07455864,-0.02228821,0.08540779,0.04475866,-0.02553628,0.02183419,0.02025144,0.00726290,-0.00579734,-0.01420625,-0.01037194,0.06716821,-0.01622870,-0.02042408,-0.05979628,-0.06396093,-0.00967050,-0.03658370,-0.05699567,-0.00059277,-0.02482632,0.03310118,0.03145880,-0.03937568,-0.02127259,-0.06018222,0.04349197,0.06065848,-0.00824993,0.05739510,0.02202510,0.08396333]',E'Allocator\n\nSelecting a non-default memory allocator when building Redis is done by setting the `MALLOC` environment variable. Redis is compiled and linked against libc malloc by default, except for jemalloc being the default on Linux systems. This default was picked because jemalloc has proven to have fewer fragmentation problems than libc malloc.\n\nTo force compiling against libc malloc, use:\n\n```sh\nmake MALLOC=libc\n```\n\nTo compile against jemalloc on Mac OS X systems, use:\n\n```sh\nmake MALLOC=jemalloc\n```','{"source": "redis", "version": "7.4", "language": "nosql", "title": "Readme", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/redis/redis/blob/unstable/README.md", "topics": "redis,README", "categories": "database,nosql,cache"}');
